

GDI 		- PCLinuxOS desktop environment installation manager.
			- Designed for PCLinuxOS system.

#       Name:     GDI   - Graphical Desktop Installer
#       Version:  19
#       License:  GNU GPL v3
#                 https://gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html
#		Date:     14.12.2015


#======================================================
	This version is alpha still, so something can fail,
	or remove needed packages from system and broke.
#======================================================


		== IMPORTANT DEPENDENCIES ==
/etc/X11/dm/Sessions/*
gdm
gtkdialog
bash
sh
awk
sed
grep
ls
cut
apt




========= HOW RUN: =========

		gksu ./gdi

			or just from root

		./gdi



========= LOGS: =========
- Logs are created in 
  /var/log/gdi
- Only about last 5 logs are saved, other are removed.
  You can change it in "functions" file. 
  (  line 85:     # Maximum number of files to keep  )


========= WARNINGS: =========
- This software is dependent on repository,
  this mean, make not work if repository was changed.
- When you install Lxde, part OpenBox will also installed,
  when you will uninstall OpenBox you will remove Lxde.



========= Tips: ===========
# How list packages from task
apt-cache depends task-kde4 | cut -d" " -f4

# How list all Desktop Enviroments:
ls /etc/X11/dm/Sessions/
grep -h "Name=" /etc/X11/dm/Sessions/* | cut -c 6-

# list from 64bit to 32 bit
sed 's/lib64/lib/'



